Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-sweeping-us-these-are-companies-making-cuts-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Jittery%20CEOs%20eager%20to%20please%20Wall%20Street%20%E2%80%94%20and%20their%20boards%20%E2%80%94%20could%20decide%20to%20make%20the%20kind%20of%20sweeping%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fintel-stock-price-layoffs-weak-guidance-missed-analyst-estimates-semiconductors-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecuts%20that%20Intel%20recently%20announced%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weaker-than-expected%20July%20jobs%20report%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-crash-picks-up-recession-fears-carry-trade-unwind-2024-8%3F_gl%3D1*3q9341*_ga*MTQ4ODgzMzg4MC4xNzEzNTI5NTU1*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcyMjg5MDg2MC4yMjEuMC4xNzIyODkwODYxLjU5LjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espooking%20investors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20could%20give%20some%20employers%20cover%20to%20step%20back%20from%20everything%20from%20a%20shorter%20week%2C%20remote%20work%2C%20and%20other%20measures%20aimed%20at%20improving%20employee%20well-being%2C%20labor%20market%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Cappelli%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20Wharton%20Business%20School%2C%20said%20that%20there%20was%20a%20perception%20that%20some%20employers%20had%20used%20layoffs%20as%20a%20cudgel%20to%20pull%20workers%20back%20into%20the%20office.%20And%20he%20said%20bosses%20could%20use%20the%20latest%20headlines%20about%20the%20economy%20as%20a%20fresh%20reason%20to%20get%20tough%20with%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20business%20is%20still%20doing%20OK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20about%20the%20reality%20as%20much%20as%20the%20perception%2C%26quot%3B%20Cappelli%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20while%20many%20workers%20in%20recent%20years%20gained%20some%20leverage%2C%20employers%20have%20s