kers%20to%20come%20in%20on%20a%20sixth%20day.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20huge%20norm%20break.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20the%20shift%20in%20Greece%20was%20more%20focused%20on%20letting%20workers%20have%20overtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fa04bf0f-9a7d-42cc-8a71-b22ae44968e1%5C%22%3ECEOs'%20safe%20space%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBrigid%20Schulte%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Better%20Life%20Lab%20at%20New%20America%20and%20author%20of%20the%20forthcoming%20book%20%26quot%3BOver%20Work%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20when%20worries%20about%20the%20economy%20pop%20up%2C%20many%20leaders%20want%20to%20return%20to%20familiar%20ways%20of%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20times%20of%20uncertainty%2C%20particularly%20leadership%20wants%20to%20go%20back%20to%20sort%20of%20what%20feels%20like%20a%20safer%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20irony%20there%20is%20that%20that%20way%20wasn't%20necessarily%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchulte%20said%20that%20companies%20that%20decide%20to%20dump%20all%20of%20their%20economic%20problems%20on%20workers%20are%20short-sighted.%20She%20noted%20that%20research%20shows%20that%20layoffs%20do%20long-term%20damage%20to%20a%20company.%20And%2C%20Schulte%20said%2C%20longer%20work%20hours%20are%20associated%20with%20lower%20productivity%2C%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployee-wellbeing-programs-help-companies-perform-better-and-manage-cost-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburnout%2C%20and%20presenteeism%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchulte%20said%20too%20often%2C%20when%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20downturn%20looms%2C%20leaders%20see%20their%20workers%20as%20a%20big%20cost%20on%20their%20balance%20sheet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTaking%20that%20longer-term%20view%20is%20actually%20going%20to%20be%20better%20for%20people%20and%20for%20your%20business%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20companies%20use%20economic%20worries%20to%20reverse%20course%20on%20efforts%20like%20flexible%20work%20arrangements%20or%20to%20conduct%20layoffs%2C%20they%20put%20their%20own%20well-being%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20end%20up%20really%20damaging%20the%20trust%20and%20morale%20at%20your%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20Schulte%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%2C%20really%2C%20you're%20only%20as%20good%20as%20your%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-fears-job-cuts-employers-less-flexible-with-workers-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722938822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b1184d393cd3c8629b5b98%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-fears-job-cuts-employers-less-flexible-with-workers-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Economic%20concerns%20could%20push%20CEOs%20to%20conduct%20layoffs%20and%20cut%20back%20on%20perks%20like%20remote%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-fears-job-cuts-employers-less-flexible-with-workers-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20boomer%20who%20moved%20from%20Minnesota%20to%20Mexico%20said%20his%20cost%20of%20living%20dropped%20by%2050%25%20%E2%80%94%20but%20transplants%20need%20to%20respect%20the%20culture%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mark%20LeGeros%20on%20his%20bicycle%20in%20Mexico%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66abf174393cd3c8629abed5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMark%20LeGeros%2C%20pictured%20on%20his%20bike%2C%20loves%20living%20in%20Mexico.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20LeGeros%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigc