20area%2C%20this%20was%20the%20highest%20share%20among%20the%2040%20large%20US%20metro%20areas%20SmartAsset%20analyzed.%20The%20median%20property%20value%20for%20these%202%2C266%20new%20Gen%20Z%20homeowners%20in%20Indianapolis%20was%20%24225%2C000%2C%20while%20the%20median%20income%20was%20%2465%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20slightly%20lower%20percentage%20of%20Gen%20Z%20bought%20homes%20in%20St.%20Louis%20last%20year%20at%20just%20below%201.6%25%20or%202%2C649%20people.%20The%20median%20property%20value%20for%20this%20demographic%2C%20who%20earned%20a%20median%20of%20%2463%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20was%20%24185%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20metro%20areas%20seeing%20higher%20rates%20of%20new%20Gen%20Z%20homeowners%20included%20Jacksonville%2C%20Virginia%20Beach%2C%20and%20Kansas%20City.%20Homebuyers%20in%20Detroit%2C%20Cleveland%2C%20and%20Pittsburgh%20bought%20homes%20typically%20below%20%24200%2C000%20with%20median%20incomes%20below%20%2465%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%2C%20with%20some%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffastest-growing-cities-in-us-ranked-in-texas-the-south-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efastest-growing%20cities%20and%20towns%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%2C%20had%20no%20metro%20areas%20in%20the%20top%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESan%20Francisco%2C%20New%20York%20City%2C%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20and%20Boston%20had%20the%20lowest%20rates%20of%20new%20Gen%20Z%20homeowners%20at%20around%200.1%25%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20median%20home%20value%20for%20new%20Gen%20Z%20homeowners%20surpassing%20%241%20million%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20In%20fact%2C%20just%2093%20homes%20were%20purchased%20by%20Gen%20Z%20in%20San%20Francisco%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eab1290b-7e59-4659-9a1b-75f4b82ce4ba%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Gen%20Z%20may%20be%20luckier%20than%20older%20generations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20whole%2C%20Gen%20Z%20may%20be%20more%20equipped%20than%20millennials%20at%20a%20similar%