yment-rate-jobs-report-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enear-perfect%20record%20is%20flashing%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20its%20creator%20told%20Business%20Insider%20this%20could%20be%20one%20of%20the%20rare%20times%20it's%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20economy%20is%20still%20growing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Claudia%20Sahm%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20New%20Century%20Advisors%2C%20a%20former%20Federal%20Reserve%20economist%2C%20and%20the%20creator%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-interest-rate-cuts-coming-crash-landing-unemployment-data-2024-8%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Sahm%2520Rule%2520is%2520triggered%2C%2522things%2520are%2520slowing%2520down.%2522%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Sahm%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20still%20adding%20jobs.%20We%20are%20spending%20even%20after%20inflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sahm%20rule%20says%20that%20the%20US%20is%20in%20a%20recession%20when%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20unemployment%20rate's%20three-month%20moving%20average%20is%20at%20least%200.50%20percentage%20points%20above%20the%20previous%2012-month%20low%2C%20again%20using%20the%20three-month%20moving%20average.%20It%20was%20triggered%20when%20the%20July%20jobs%20report%20on%20Friday%20showed%20unemployment%20had%20jumped%20to%204.3%25.%20The%20US%20economy%20added%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-rate-job-growth-july-labor-market-economic-data-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E114%2C000%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%2C%20falling%20short%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investing.com%2Feconomic-calendar%2Fnonfarm-payrolls-227%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20expectations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20rebuking%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20US%20is%20in%20a%20recession%2C%20Sahm%20does%20have%20concerns%20about%20the%20labor%20market%20and%20high%20interest%20rates.%20She%20said%20data%20from%20the%20latest%20jobs%20report%20%26quot%3Bcertainly%20raises%20chances%20of%20going%20into%20a%20recession%26quot%3B%20if%20things%20don't%20get%20sorted%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20lever%20to%20pull%20is%20to%20normalize%20interest%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20Sahm%20said%2C%20joining%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-timeline-federal-reserve-inflation-powell-economists-forecast-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echorus%20of%20economists%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20say%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20waited%20too%20long%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-likely-september-federal-reserve-holds-steady-july-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed%20decided%20to%20hold%20interest%20rates%20steady%20in%20its%20July%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarket%20traders%20still%20expect%20cuts%20in%20September%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20although%20some%20have%20called%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femergency-interest-rate-cut-likelihood-recession-outlook-stock-market-crash-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency%20rate%20cut%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20early%20as%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%2C%20including%20Sahm%2C%20say%20the%20Fed%20should've%20seen%20the%20signs.%20It's%20not%20surprising%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20has%20cooled%20after%20the%20booming%20post-pandemic%20recovery.%20Sahm%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20expected%20and%20probably%20necessary%20to%20see%20things%20get%20back%20to%20a%20more%20quote%2C%20unquote%20normal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20said%2C%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20going%20beyond%20%26quot%3Bnormal%26quot%3B%20now.%2