s%20came%20easily%2C%20and%20tech's%20valuations%20skyrocketed%20as%20companies%20%26quot%3Bdisrupted%26quot%3B%20incumbent%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmart%20people%20wanted%20to%20work%20at%20these%20companies%20to%20tackle%20the%20world's%20most%20intractable%20problems%2C%20and%20average%20Americans%20began%20to%20integrate%20the%20best%20solutions%20into%20their%20everyday%20lives.%20It%20seemed%20like%20every%20new%20idea%20opened%20up%20a%20new%20market%20worth%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20%E2%80%94%20smartphones%2C%20social%20media%2C%20cloud%20computing%2C%20software%20development%20solutions.%20Liquid%20capital%2C%20growing%20market%20dominance%2C%20slick%20ads%2C%20and%20fawning%20media%20made%20it%20easy%20for%20giants%20like%20Google%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20Amazon%20to%20expand%20their%20footprint%20and%20grow%20their%20bottom%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20like%20any%20decaying%20relationship%2C%20these%20companies%20got%20lazy%2C%20entitled%2C%20and%20demanding.%20They%20started%20to%20care%20less%20about%20the%20foundations%20of%20their%20business%20%E2%80%94%20like%20having%20happy%20customers%20and%20stable%20products%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20about%20making%20themselves%20feel%20better%20by%20reinforcing%20their%20monopolies.%20By%20around%202015%2C%20tech's%20cool-dad%20period%20had%20ended.%20After%20reaping%20the%20rewards%20of%20various%20hyper-growth%20ideas%2C%20the%20industry's%20growth%20promises%20began%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20its%20ability%20to%20innovate.%20Silicon%20Valley%20became%20addicted%20to%20acquisitions%2C%20buying%20the%20new%2C%20hot%20toy%20that%20it%20figured%20everyone%20would%20like%20instead%20of%20thinking%20through%20what%20Americans%20actually%20needed.%20Instead%20of%20doing%20the%20work%20to%20get%20better%2C%20tech%20has%20remained%20steadfastly%20attached%20to%20the%20tropes%20that%20worked%20when%20its%20products%20were%20at%20their%20prime.%20The%20industry%20has%20become%20a%20bloated%2C%20surly%20divorced%20dad%20who%20refuses%20to%20do%20the%20hard%20work%20and%20look%20inward%20to%20find%20real%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20players%20in%20tech%20are%20dyeing%20their%20gray%20hairs%2C%20starting%20a%20band%20with%20their%20equally%20middle-aged%20friends%2C%20throwing%20on%20a%20leather%20jacket%20or%20new%20chain%20(sometimes%20literally)%2C%20and%20trying%20anything%20to%20pretend%20that%20they've%20%26quot%3Bstill%20got%20it%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20anything%20other%20than%20focusing%20on%20building%20important%20and%20meaningful%20products%20that%20users%20actually%20want.%20Big%20Tech%20has%20decided%20the%20way%20to%20keep%20customers%20isn't%20to%20compete%20or%20provide%20them%20with%20a%20better%20service%20but%20instead%20make%20it%20hard%20to%20leave%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-instacart-uses-dark-patterns-encourage-shoppers-buy-faster-more-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrick%20customers%20into%20buying%20things%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20eradicate%20competition%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-companies-ruining-apps-websites-internet-worse-google-facebook-amazon-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eso%20that%20it%20can%20make%20things%20as%20profitable%20as%20possible%2C%20even%20if%20the%20experience%20is%20worse%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Great%20companies%20are%20able%20to%20accept%20their%20limitations%20and%20acknowledge%20that%20nobody%20%3Cem%3Ehas%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20your%20customer%2C%20but%20giants%20like%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Amazon%20refuse%20to%20accept%20that%20they%20can't%20do%20everything%20and%20that%20their%20problems%20are%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20the%20kind%20of%20lack%20of%20introspection%20and%20cultural%20laziness%20that%20breaks%20relationships.%20Customers%20have%20spent%20the%20past%2030%20years%20sharing%20their%20precious%20data%20and%20money%20with%20tech%20companies%2C%20but%20Sili