ww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-elon-musk-microchips-brains-ai-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeuralink%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20successfully%20implanted%20another%20brain%20chip%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-claims-first-human-patient-received-neuralink-implant-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman%20patient.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20owner%20made%20the%20comments%20during%20an%20episode%20of%20the%20Lex%20Fridman%20podcast%20released%20on%20Friday%2C%20which%20lasted%20more%20than%20eight%20hours.%20Musk%20said%20that%20400%20of%20the%20implant's%20electrodes%20on%20the%20second%20patient's%20brain%20are%20working.%20The%20threads%20have%20more%20than%201%2C000%20electrodes%20in%20total.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink%20aims%20to%20eventually%20create%20a%20device%20that%20would%20allow%20people%20to%20do%20anything%20with%20their%20minds%2C%20from%20communicating%20telepathically%20to%20playing%20video%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-brain-chip-implant-first-human-patient-what-its-like-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EIts%20first%20patient%2C%20Noland%20Arbaugh%2C%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereceived%20the%20brain%20chip%20in%20January.%20He%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20implant%20had%20helped%20him%20regain%20independence%20and%20reconnect%20socially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20brain%20chip%20company%20has%20lofty%20goals%20%E2%80%94%20here's%20how%20the%20chips%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e73693b-6954-491d-a980-ab59579767bf%5C%22%3EBrain-machine%20interface%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink's%20overarching%20aim%20is%20to%20create%20a%20brain-machine%20interface%20that%20could%20revolutionize%20how%20humans%20interact%20with%20technology%20and%20potentially%20lead%20to%20groundbreaking%20advancements%20in%20medicine%2C%20communication%2C%20and%20human%20cognition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Musk%20said%20on%20the%20podcast%20that%20someone%20with%20a%20Neuralink%20chip%20could%20beat%20a%20professional%20gamer%20in%20a%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20feel%20pretty%20confident%20that%20in%20the%20next%20year%20or%20two%2C%20someone%20with%20a%20Neuralink%20implant%20would%20be%20able%20to%20outperform%20a%20pro%20gamer%20because%20the%20reaction%20time%20would%20be%20faster%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20core%20of%20Neuralink's%20technology%20is%20a%20small%2C%20implantable%20chip%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.captechu.edu%2Fblog%2Fneuralinks-brain-chip-how-it-works-and-what-it-means%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20%26quot%3BLink%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20contains%20numerous%20tiny%2C%20flexible%20electrode%20threads.%20The%20threads%20are%20thinner%20than%20human%20hair%20and%20require%20precise%20surgery%2C%20which%20is%20performed%20by%20a%20specialized%20robotic%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chip%20captures%20and%20transmits%20brain%20activity%2C%20sending%20it%20wirelessly%20to%20an%20external%20device%20such%20as%20a%20computer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20of%20Neuralink%20devices%20is%20to%20eventually%20be%20able%20to%20repair%20damaged%20neurons%20and%20help%20people%20with%20issues%20such%20as%20paralysis.%20However%2C%20the%20company%20has%20faced%20a%20long%20road%20to%20get%20its%20products%20into%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a77f6da-2f1a-469e-8159-49837cd1b7e3%5C%22%3ERobot%20surgery%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20threads%20are%20too%20small%20to%20be%20implanted%20by%20a%20human%20hand%2C%20so%20the%20surgery%20is%20done%20with%20a%20robot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Neuralink%2C%20the%20robot%20can%20handle%20the%20ultrathin%20wires%20and%20implant%20them%20without%20disrupting%20blood%20vessels%20in%20the%20brain%2C%20reducing%20the%20risk%20of%20damage%20and%20inflammation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20reportedl