20its%20innovation.%20It%20made%20sense%20to%20come%20out%20with%20products%20that%20were%20unexpected.%20It%20was%20a%20different%20way%20of%20imagining%20things%20and%20creating%20a%20better%20product%20without%20100%20years%20of%20design%20bloat%2C%20but%20I%20think%20it's%20gotten%20to%20the%20point%20where%20it%20feels%20forced.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Model%20S%20and%20Model%20X%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-offers-round-steering-wheel-option-yoke-replacement-complaints-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esteering%20yoke%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20seemed%20like%20the%20point%20wasn't%20to%20design%20something%20better.%20It%20was%20just%20a%20gimmick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-cars-starting-to-look-basic-sales-problem-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eignored%20traditional%20automaker%20strategies%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20way%20that%2C%20I%20think%2C%20has%20been%20detrimental%20to%20the%20brand.%20The%202021%20Model%20S%20and%20Model%20X%20refreshes%20were%20designed%20to%20make%20them%20look%20the%20same%20as%20the%20old%20models.%20They%20didn't%20want%20to%20cater%20to%20an%20industry%20that%20has%20these%20refreshes.%20The%20statement%20was%3A%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20like%20the%20classic%20design%20forever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20know%20when%20the%20tipping%20point%20was%2C%20but%20it%20turned%20from%20this%20fresh%20and%20innovative%20strategy%20to%20Tesla%20trying%20to%20convince%20customers%20this%20is%20what%20they%20actually%20want%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20it%20reflects%20consumer%20interests%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20decision%20to%20leave%20Tesla%20came%20down%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20factors%20that%20had%20been%20slowly%20creeping%20up%20on%20me%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years.%20If%20I'd%20had%20a%20better%20commute%20and%20a%20job%20that%20I%20liked%2C%20I%20might%20have%20been%20able%20to%20shrug%20it%20all%20off%20and%20tell%20myself%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%20matter%20what%20crazy%20stuff%20is%20Musk%20doing%20now%2C%20I'm%20just%20going%20to%20put%20my%20head%20down%20and%20keep%20working.%26quot%3B%20But%20with%20the%20layoffs%2C%20it%20all%20came%20to%20a%20head%20at%20once%3A%20I%20wasn't%20happy%20with%20what%20I%20was%20doing%20anymore%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20feel%20like%20I%20had%20faith%20in%20Musk's%20plans%20for%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChoosing%20to%20leave%20was%20really%20difficult.%20I%20put%20my%20whole%20life%20into%20that%20job%20%E2%80%94%20I%20moved%20three%20times%20and%20worked%20at%20five%20locations%2C%20supporting%2035%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20felt%20like%20a%20divorce%2C%20but%20I%20think%20I%20made%20the%20right%20choice.%20I've%20moved%20on%20now%2C%20and%20my%20spouse%20and%20I%20have%20decided%20to%20start%20our%20own%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETesla%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20Tesla%20or%20have%20a%20tip%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20the%20reporter%20via%20a%20non-work%20email%20and%20device%20at%20gkay%40businessinsider.com%20or%20248-894-6012.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-i-resigned-quit-employee-worker-elon-musk-why-explained-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722934862000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b120c1b4912df3ae18fc04%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-i-resigned-quit-employee-worker-elon-musk-why-explained-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Tesla%20employee%20who%20had%20worked%20there%20for%20nearly%20eight%20years%20says%20a%20lack%20of%20faith%20in%20Elon%20Musk's%20leadership%20finally%20pressed%20them%20to%20quit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gkay%40businessinsider.com%20(Grace%20Kay)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A222%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-i-resigned-quit-employee-worker-elon-musk-why-explained-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ashwini%20Ponnappa's%20Fiery%20Reply%20To%20Prakash%20Padukone's%20Criticism%20Of%20Lakshya%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EVenting%20out%20his%20frustration%20at%20Indian%20badminton%20stars'%20near-misses%20in%20the%20Paris%20Olympic%20Games%2C%20Prakash%20Padukone%20on%20Monday%20said%20it's%20high%20time%20that%20players%20learn%20to%20withstand%20pressure%2C%20become%20accountable%20and%20start%20delivering%20results%20after%20receiving%20support.%20Padukone's%20comments%20came%20after%20Lakshya%20Sen%20succumbed%20to%20pressure%20in%20his%20bronze%20medal%20match%20against%20Lee%20Zii%20Jia%2C%20meaning%20the%20entire%20Indian%20badminton%20contingent%20drew%20a%20blank%20at%20the%20Paris%20Games.%20However%2C%20Indian%20shuttler%20Ashwini%20Ponnappa%2C%20a%20part%20of%20India's%20badminton%20contingent%20in%20the%202024%20Olympics%2C%20isn't%20happy%20seeing%20Padukone%20throwing%20shuttles%20under%20the%20bus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDisappointing%20to%20see%20this.%20If%20a%20player%20wins%2C%20everyone%20jumps%20on%20the%20bandwagon%20to%20take%20credit%2C%20and%20if%20they%20lose%2C%20it's%20just%20the%20player's%20fault%3F!%26quot%3B%20Ponnappa%20wrote%20in%20an%20Instagram%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20aren't%20coaches%20held%20responsible%20for%20lack%20of%20preparation%20and%20getting%20the%20player%20ready%3F%20They%20are%20the%20first%20ones%20to%20take%20credit%20for%20wins%3B%20why%20not%20take%20responsibility%20for%20their%20players'%20losses%20as%20well%3F%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20winning%20takes%20team%20effort%20and%20losing%20is%20also%20the%20team's%20responsibility.%20You%20can't%20suddenly%20push%20the%20player%20under%20the%20bus%20and%20blame%20it%20all%20on%20the%20player.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EAshwini%20Ponnappa's%20two%20cents%20on%20yesterday's%20statement%20where%20Padukone%20sir%20indirectly%20gave%20a%20stern%20message%20to%20Lakshya%20and%20the%20other%20athletes.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F3aDYw0loJT%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F3aDYw0loJT%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Valmoth%20(%40valmoth1)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fvalmoth1%2Fstatus%2F1820716149870338285%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%206%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20All%20England%20champion%20said%20India%20must%20focus%20on%20giving%20mind%20training%20to%20its%20athletes%2C%20so%20that%20they%20can%20learn%20to%20counter%20pressure%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20suggested%20that%20there%20must%20be%20a%20system%20in%20place%2C%20like%20it%20is%20in%20China%2C%20where%20they%20do%20not%20depend%20on%20one%20player%20and%20succeed%20in%20churning%20out%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20remain%20satisfied%20just%20having%20one%20player.%20We%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20next%20line%2C%20maybe%20even%20the%20third%20line.%20Like%20they%20do%20in%20cricket.%20You%20have%20the%20main%20team%2C%20then%20the%20'A'%20team%2C%20then%20the%20under-19%20team%2C%20under-17%20team.%20So%20we%20need%20to%20focus.%20There%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20talent%2C%20there%20is%20absolutely%20no%20doubt%20but%20a%20combined%20effort%20is%20required%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20effort%20from%20the%20players%20also.%20A%20little%20more%20responsibility%2C%20a%20little%20more%20accountability.%20Not%20just%20ask%20for%20whatever%20you%20ask%20for.%20Once%20you%20are%20given%20that%2C%20you%20also%20have%20to%20be%20accountable.%20I%20think%20the%20players%20have%20to%20learn%20to%20take%20responsibility.%26quot%3B%20Sen%20squandered%20an%20opening%20game%20advantage%20and%20an%208-3%20lead%20in%20the%20second%20to%20go%20down%2021-13%2016-21%2011-21%20to%20Malaysia's%20Lee%20Zii%20Jia%20in%20the%2071-minute%20clash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPadukone%20said%20the%2022-year-old%20from%20Almora%20needs%20both%20--%20mind%20training%20as%20well%20game%20improvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20needs%20to%20work%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20when%20he's%20playing%20with%20the%20wind.%20Everybody%20has%20a%20problem%20but%20I%20think%20he%20has%20more%20problem%20than%20others.%20If%20you%20saw%20the%20first%20game%2C%20the%20Malaysian%20played%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20and%20went%20out.%20You%20were%20not%20able%20to%20control%20so%20it%20happens%20but%20you%20must%20learn%20to%20control%20and%20make%20less%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMistakes%20will%20happen%2C%20everybody%20is%20comfortable%20playing%20against%20the%20wind%20because%20you%20can%20play%20freely%20without%20any%20hesitation%20but%20Lakshya%20probably%20needs%20both.%20A%20little%20bit%20of%20mind%20training%20and%20the%20focus%20on%20mind%20training%20plus%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20practice%20and%20a%20little%20better%20control%20he%20needs%20to%20work%20on%20the%20court%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%20For%20Padukone%2C%20it%20was%20pressure%20that%20got%20to%20Sen%2C%20who%20wilted%20when%20Lee%20unleashed%20his%20power-packed%20strokes.%20%26quot%3BEarlier%20we%20were%20not%20even%20getting%20to%20number%20four.%20One%20thing%20is%20very%20clear%2C%20we%20need%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20mind%20training.%20We%20don't%20give%20enough%20attention%20for%20sports%20psychology%20which%20is%20very%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Padukone%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20Olympics%2C%20if%20you've%20seen%20a%20lot%20of%20top%20players%20have%20all%20lost%2C%20not%20because%20they%20were%20not%20good%20technically%20or%20physically%20but%20because%20they%20couldn't%20handle%20the%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOlympics%20is%20all%20about%20handling%20pressure%20so%20all%20the%20more%20important%20that%20we%20pay%20more%20attention%20to%20mind%2C%20do%20meditation%2C%20yoga.%26quot%3B%20Padukone%20felt%20that%20shooter%20Manu%20Bhaker%20probably%20could%20do%20well%20because%20she%20was%20not%20under%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20who%20are%20favorites%20are%20always%20under%20pressure%20and%20have%20not%20done%20so%20well%20as%20expected.%20Most%20of%20our%20medals%20even%20in%20the%20earlier%20Olympics%20have%20come%20from%20people%20whom%20we%20have%20not%20expected%20anything%20because%20there%20is%20no%20pressure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20have%20roped%20in%20several%20foreign%20coaches%20and%20Padukone%2C%20who%20trains%20PV%20Sindhu%2C%20said%20it's%20time%20that%20India%20bring%20sports%20psychologists%20from%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20high%20time%20we%20have%20foreign%20sports%20psychologists%20also.%20This%20is%20not%20to%20take%20away%20anything%20from%20the%20Indian%20sports%20psychologist.%20Some%20of%20them%20are%20good%20but%20I%20think%20high%20time%20you%20know%20the%20players%20also%20realise%20the%20importance%20of%20sports%20psychology%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20cannot%20be%20done%20just%20three%20months%20before%20the%20Olympics%20or%20if%20somebody%20wants%20to%20do%20well%20in%20the%20next%20Olympics%20they%20have%20to%20start%20right%20now%20and%20be%20at%20it%20throughout%20only%20then%20will%20it%20make%20a%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20PTI%20Inputs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722934320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fcnfcrluo_ponappa-x_625x300_06_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Folympics-2024%2Fcant-pus