22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722926614000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-112309022%2Cimgsize-1949155.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbangladesh-crisis-key-developments-protesters-name-muhammad-yunus-as-chief-adviser-to-proposed-interim-government%2Farticleshow%2F112307039.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20WORLD%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbangladesh-crisis-key-developments-protesters-name-muhammad-yunus-as-chief-adviser-to-proposed-interim-government%2Farticleshow%2F112307039.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Is%20Nahid%20Islam%2C%20Student%20Leader%20Who%20Led%20Protests%20Against%20Sheikh%20Hasina%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20nearly%20a%20month%20of%20anti-quota%20and%20anti-government%20demonstrations%20that%20swept%20across%20Bangladesh%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20resigned%20and%20fled%20the%20country.%20Her%20resignation%20came%20in%20the%20face%20of%20countrywide%20demonstrations%20led%20by%20student%20leader%20Nahid%20Islam.%20What%20started%20as%20a%20call%20for%20reform%20in%20the%20country's%20quota%20policy%20for%20the%20families%20of%20freedom%20fighters%20slowly%20morphed%20into%20an%20anti-government%20movement%20demanding%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20resignation.%20%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnOn%20Monday%2C%20protesters%20defied%20a%20nationwide%20curfew%2C%20stormed%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20residence%2C%20and%20declared%20victory%20for%20the%20people's%20movement.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3ESome%20facts%20about%20student%20leader%20Nahid%20Islam%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn1.%20Nahid%20Islam%20is%20currently%20a%20student%20in%20the%20Sociology%20Department%20at%20Dhaka%20University.%C2%A0%20He%20is%20known%20for%20his%20work%20as%20a%20human%20rights%20defender.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn2.%20He%20serves%20as%20one%20of%20the%20National%20Coordinators%20for%20the%20'Students%20Against%20Discrimination'%20Movement%2C%20a%20student-led%20protest%20demanding%20reforms%20to%20the%20quota%20system%20in%20government%20jobs%20in%20Bangladesh.%20The%20movement%20began%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Bangladesh%20reinstated%20a%2030%20per%20cent%20quota%20for%20descendants%20of%20war%20veterans%20and%20freedom%20fighters%20in%20June%202024.%20The%20movement%20argued%20the%20quota%20was%20a%20discriminatory%20and%20politically%20manipulated%20system%20to%20access%20government%20jobs.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn3.%20Mr%20Nahid%20has%20been%20vocal%20against%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20party%2C%20the%20Awami%20League%2C%20describing%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Bterrorists%26quot%3B%20deployed%20on%20the%20roads.%20Previously%2C%20addressing%20protesters%20at%20Shahbagh%2C%20he%20declared%20students%20had%20%26quot%3Bpicked%20up%20sticks%20today%26quot%3B%20and%20were%20ready%20to%20%26quot%3Btake%20up%20arms%26quot%3B%20if%20sticks%20didn't%20work.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn4.%20On%2019%20July%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontlinedefenders.org%2Fen%2Fprofile%2Fnahid-islam%C2%A0%5C%22%3ENahid%20Islam%20was%20abducted%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20at%20least%2025%20men%20in%20plain%20clothes%20from%20a%20house%20in%20Sabujbagh.%20He%20was%20blindfolded%2C%20handcuffed%20and%20tortured%20during%20repeated%20interrogations%20about%20his%20involvement%20in%20the%20protests.%20Two%20days%20later%2C%20he%20was%20found%20unconscious%20and%20battered%20under%20a%20bridge%20in%20Purbachal.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn5.%20Nahid%20Islam%20was%20kidnapped%20a%20second%20time%20on%2026%20July%202024%20from%20Gonoshasthaya%20Nagar%20Hospital%20in%20Dhanmondi.%20Individuals%20claiming%20to%20be%20from%20various%20intelligence%20agencies%2C%20including%20the%20Dhaka%20Metropolitan%20Police's%20Detective%20Branch%2C