ent%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20secrets%20of%20the%20CIA's%20black%20sites%20have%20long%20been%20hidden.%20But%20now%2C%20a%20disturbing%20photo%20showing%20Amar%20Al-Baluchi%2C%20a%209%2F11%20suspect%2C%20shackled%2C%20malnourished%2C%20and%20naked%20in%20a%20CIA%20black%20site%2C%20has%20emerged%2C%20revealing%20the%20harsh%20reality%20of%20life%20inside%20these%20secret%20prisons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20image%2C%20shared%20by%20his%20lawyers%2C%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20from%202004%2C%20when%20al-Baluchi%20was%2026%20years%20old%20and%20likely%20taken%20at%20the%20CIA's%20secret%20prison%20in%20Bucharest%2C%20Romania.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20CIA%20black%20site%20is%20a%20secret%20prison%20or%20detention%20centre%20operated%20by%20the%20CIA%20outside%20the%20US%2C%20where%20terrorism%20suspects%20are%20held%20and%20interrogated.%20These%20facilities%20are%20not%20registered%20with%20any%20government%20or%20international%20organisation%2C%20and%20their%20existence%20is%20not%20publicly%20acknowledged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmar%20Al-Baluchi%20has%20been%20held%20at%20Guantanamo%20Bay%20since%202006%2C%20without%20being%20convicted%20of%20a%20crime.%20He%20was%20first%20arrested%20in%20Karachi%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20in%202003%20and%20secretly%20transferred%20between%20five%20black%20sites%20before%20being%20sent%20to%20Guantanamo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20photo%20to%20emerge%20from%20the%20CIA's%20black%20sites%2C%20where%20hundreds%20of%20prisoners%20were%20held%20and%20interrogated.%20The%20image%20was%20released%20through%20a%20classification%20review%20process%20at%20the%20military%20commissions%20and%20was%20first%20published%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2Farticle%2F2024%2Faug%2F02%2Fseptember-11-detainee-cia-black-site-photo%C2%A0%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20photo%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20one%20of%20hundreds%20taken%20by%20the%20CIA%2C%20showing%20prisoners%20being%20stripped%20and%20photographed%20as%20they%20were%20moved%20through%20the%20black%20site%20programme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20photo%20sheds%20light%20on%20the%20CIA's%20secret%20detention%20programme%2C%20which%20held%20at%20least%20119%20Muslim%20men%20between%202002%20and%202008.%20Thirty-nine%20of%20them%20were%20subjected%20to%20%26quot%3Benhanced%20interrogation%20techniques%26quot%3B%2C%20later%20admitted%20by%20the%20US%20government%20to%20be%20torture.%20Despite%20this%2C%20no%20one%20at%20the%20CIA%20has%20been%20held%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAl-Baluchi%20was%20subjected%20to%20forced%20nudity%2C%20%26quot%3Bwalling%26quot%3B%20(repeatedly%20bouncing%20his%20head%20off%20a%20wall)%2C%20sleep%20deprivation%2C%20physical%20abuse%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20torture.%20He%20was%20used%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btraining%20prop%26quot%3B%20for%20student%20interrogators%20to%20practice%20their%20techniques.%20He%20lost%2010%20kgs%20in%20just%20a%20few%20months%20and%20may%20have%20suffered%20permanent%20traumatic%20brain%20injury%20due%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bwalling%26quot%3B%20technique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CIA%20took%20approximately%2014%2C000%20photographs%20of%20detainees%20in%20their%20black%20sites%2C%20but%20only%20a%20few%20have%20been%20declassified.%20The%20existence%20of%20these%20photos%20was%20hidden%20until%202015%2C%20and%20most%20remain%20classified.%20Defence%20attorneys%20have%20fought%20for%20years%20to%20release%20more%20material%2C%20gradually%20uncovering%20evidence%20of%20the%20CIA's%20torture%20program%2C%20showing%20prisoners%20being%20stripped%20and%20photographed%20as%20they%20were%20moved%20through%20the%20black%20site%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDaniel%20J%20Jones%2C%20the%20lead%20investigator%20in%20the%202014%20Senate%20Intelligence%20Committee%20study%2C%20described%20the%20photos%20as%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20disturbing%20and%20clear%20evidence%20of%20the%20brutality%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20black%20sites.%20He%20called%20them%20among%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20highly%20protected%20records%20of%20the%20CIA's%20torture%20program.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CIA%20destroyed%20videotapes%20of%20interrogations%20at%20a%20black%20site%20in%20Thailand%20in%202005%20to%20prevent%20their%20release.%20The%20agency's%20leadership%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20trying%20to%20conceal%20evidence%20of%20their%20torture%20program.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722924720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Ff6dev1k_cia_625x300_06_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshackled-and-naked-photo-released-of-cia-prisoner-at-black-site-6266646%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20secrets%20of%20the%20CIA's%20black%20sites%20have%20long%20been%20hidden.%20But%20now%2C%20a%20disturbing%20photo%20showing%20Amar%20Al-Baluchi%2C%20a%209%2F11%20suspect%2C%20shackled%2C%20malnourished%2C%20and%20naked%20in%20a%20CIA%20black%20site%2C%20has%20emerged%2C.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshackled-and-naked-photo-released-of-cia-prisoner-at-black-site-6266646%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sachin%20Hits%20Bulls%20Eye%2C%20Explains%20How%20Djokovic%20Beat%20Alcaraz%20In%20Olympics%20Final%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENovak%20Djokovic%20ended%20the%20long%20wait%20of%20being%20crowned%20an%20Olympics%20champion%20as%20he%20defeated%20Carlos%20Alcaraz%20in%20men's%20singles%20final%20on%20Sunday%2C%20wearing%20the%20gold%20medal%20across%20his%20neck%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20his%20career.%20The%20battle%20between%20Djokovic%20and%20Alcaraz%20was%20neck-to-neck%2C%20with%20neither%20managing%20to%20break%20the%20other.%20Both%20the%20first%20and%20the%20second%20sets%20had%20to%20be%20decided%20via%20tie-breakers%2C%20with%20the%20Serbian%20Djokovic%20prevailing%20every%20time.%20As%20India's%20batting%